runs.comm: smashed down the ground! Tsotsobe bowls a half volley outside off, Finch gets down and drills it wide of mid-off
Behardien misjudges it at deep square leg, it was a length ball that was pulled, Behardian ran to his right and over ran it but managed to stop it before going to the rope
bad ball, this was drifting down leg and length, Warner knew the fine leg was up and pulled it over him
pitched up and the bowler was lucky Warner didn't time it well,the ball drops in front of deep midwicket and rolls, the outfield's wet
shot! This was length and too straight, Warner stayed back and clubbed it with ease over deep square leg
that took an eternity to drop down and roll towards the rope, he made room and scooped that one down to deep cover, mistimed but good enough
Abbott nearly got that one to sneak through, he was back at the crease and the ball skidded and hit the top of the pad
Finch made room and Abbott followed him and cramped him up, he could only push it to the off side
Amla's done something right! Finch makes room and looks to chip that over the on side, miscues it to midwicket where Amla backpedals and takes it
take that! Abbott bowls a half volley wide outside off and he makes room and bashes it wide of mid-off and cover
he fails to connect this time, this was short and Warner made room to slog but missed it
follows it up with a fuller one and Warner plays all around, the ball clips the pad and rolls away, excellent over by Abbott
good start, full outside off and he makes room and drives to cover
well bowled, nice and straight, not much room and he angles it to the off side
Okay! That was a flat-batted thump, a length ball, duly punished, Warner read the length early and it went flat and quick over deep midwicket, on the roof and out of here
Warner wants to do this on his own, this was full and Warner looked to loft straight but got an outside edge that beat short third man
slower ball back of the hand and well adjusted by Warner, it was dropped short and he adjusted the power and placed it wide of short fine leg

awesome attempt at the boundary by Parnell! Warner scooped this one to deep cover, Parnell caught it at the edge of the rope, momentum took him back, he threw the ball back before going over, turned around and looked to catch it at the second attempt but couldn't hang on
full outside off and he gets an outside edge to third man
straight to cover! It was a low full toss, Watson made room and looked to scoop it over cover, connects off the bottom of the bat and ends up scooping to cover
Maxwell looks to clip that to the on side the ball skids and clips the pad
pacy delivery outside off and he makes room to scoop but misses it
fires that full outside off and he drills it to mid-off
Spin brings a wicket! Tossed up from round the wicket, Warner looks to play the reverse sweep, fails to connect and the ball clips his pad in front of the stumps
down the track and he pushes it to midwicket
comes round the wicket to the right-hander and he sprays it too wide, Maxwell doesn't play at it
drags it short and he pulls him down to Amla at deep midwicket
turning out to be an inspired bowling change! Duminy continues round the wicket to the right-hander, fired that full and quick outside off, Maxwell ends up driving it hard to Faf at point
ends the over with a single, he can only dab it down to short third man
and he begins the over with a no ball! Above waist high, Hodge stays back and slaps it over point
and he sprays it too wide this time, Hodge tries to dig it out outside off but misses

confusion in the calling! Hendricks does well to bowl it full on the stumps and Hodge clips it wide of midwicket, Bailey turned for the second run but Hodge wasn't interested, Miller fired the throw to de Kock  and Bailey dives in vain
full outside off and he drives to cover
another good delivery by Hendrricks and he can only clip it to mid-on
this was pitched up and Haddin scooped it over cover and it was in the air and three players went for it, mistimed
fires that full on the stumps and he can only flick it to square leg
nice finish to the over, on the pads and he can only force it to deep square leg
pitched up on middle and leg and lofted down to long-on, didn't get the distance and it goes on the bounce
well bowled! This was fired full and Haddin shuffled across the stumps and looked to force it to the on side, the ball clipped the pad and rolled away
oh well that went miles! This was pitched up on the pads, wrong length and line, swung away and that really went the distance over deep midwicket
Advantage Australia! 12 off the last two balls, a low full toss, what a time for Parnell to bowl one, swung away and this was flatter, just enough to clear deep midwicket
Hodge looks to smash this one too but it was too short and cleared the batsman and nearly cleared the keeper too, wide called, that does it for Australia
